<task id="042" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-09 CapabilityRouter dedup — one user intent → one route → one playbook → one render (eliminates R5 duplicate-fire)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>5-7 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>041, 025</dependencies>
    <blocks>048</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF code refactoring at the routing surface (`CapabilityRouter`); touches conversational primacy (NFR-01 binding); structurally fixes R5 lessons-learned Gap A (path A vs path B parallelism is a smell); requires comprehensive regression test of every CapabilityRouter route. 6+ steps; FULL rigor mandatory.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches the central `CapabilityRouter` surface — single point of routing for all chat intents. Sequential with the rest of Phase B; cannot parallelize. Also depends on Phase A task 025 (PlaybookExecutionEngine FK fix + orchestrator refactor) for the canonical route surface to exist.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Refactor `CapabilityRouter` so that one user intent maps to one route, one playbook,
    one `DeliverOutput` call, and one rendered output. This structurally eliminates the
    R5 duplicate-fire bug: typing `/summarize` no longer produces a parallel chat-agent
    response AND a workspace summary; it produces exactly ONE rendering per the
    playbook node's `destination` (set by tasks 032 + 033). R5 lessons-learned Gap A
    identified path A vs path B parallelism as a SMELL — this task structurally enforces
    "one intent → one path".

    This task depends on Phase A task 025 (Pillar 4 PlaybookExecutionEngine routing —
    chat `/summarize` routes through the engine instead of the alternate-key bypass) and
    Phase B tasks 032 + 033 (action `outputSchema` populated + node `destination`
    populated) and task 041 (schema-aware widget). The CapabilityRouter consults the
    chosen playbook's node config `destination` and picks ONE rendering surface
    (chat vs workspace vs form-prefill). The 3-tier capability routing
    (deterministic → LLM → fallback) is preserved; the FIX is at the OUTPUT routing,
    not the INTENT routing.

    NFR-01 BINDING: conversational primacy preserved. CapabilityRouter restricts the
    tool list per context but never prevents conversational ability. The dedup applies
    to OUTPUT routing only — refinement, follow-up, comparison, and context injection
    all continue to work via full conversation history.

    BFF code change: verify publish-size; report delta vs prior baseline; ≤+5 MB R6
    total budget per NFR-02.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Senior backend engineer with deep familiarity with
    `CapabilityRouter`, the 3-tier intent classification (deterministic / LLM /
    fallback), `PlaybookExecutionEngine`, `DeliverOutput` node executor, the
    `SprkChatAgentFactory` middleware pipeline, and the conversational primacy NFR-01
    binding. Capable of refactoring central routing logic without regressing tool
    behavior or conversational ability.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `CapabilityRouter` enforces one-intent-one-route-one-render structurally. Typing
    `/summarize` produces exactly ONE rendered output (per the playbook node's
    `destination`). The legacy duplicate-fire (chat ack + parallel workspace artifact
    via TWO LLM calls) is eliminated by collapsing the routing into a single
    decision: read playbook node `destination`; emit ONE PaneEventBus event /
    DeliverOutput call. Unit tests + integration test demonstrate ONE render per
    intent. Conversational primacy is preserved (NFR-01) — refinement, follow-up,
    comparison continue to work normally.
  </goal>

