  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-01">**Conversational primacy preserved (BINDING)** — LLM responds conversationally for most turns. CapabilityRouter restricts the tool list per context but never prevents conversational ability. Refinement, follow-up, comparison, context injection all work via full conversation history + memory. THE DEDUP APPLIES TO OUTPUT ROUTING ONLY; the LLM's conversational surface is unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">**R5 Lessons-Learned Gap A (Path A vs Path B parallelism is a smell)** — this task structurally enforces "one intent → one path". Cross-reference `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/lessons-learned.md` Gap A. Document the structural fix in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI as BFF extension + PublicContracts facade boundary — if the dedup requires a new facade method, it goes through `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/`; do NOT inject AI-internal types into CRUD-side code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — no new top-level DI registrations; new services register inside existing modules.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — measure delta vs prior baseline; report in task notes; ≤+5 MB R6 total budget per NFR-02.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">AI data governance — execution events log tool names + decisions + timestamps ONLY; never user message text. If CapabilityRouter telemetry is touched, preserve this.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus 4-channel preserved; no 5th channel. CapabilityRouter consults node config but does NOT add new channels.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">Safety pipeline preserved (PromptShield + Groundedness + Citations + Privilege + Cross-matter via SafetyPipelineMiddleware). CapabilityRouter changes flow through the existing middleware chain unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-30">CapabilityRouter dedup — `chat` returns text/markdown inline; `workspace` publishes PaneEventBus events with configured widgetType; `form-prefill` routes to wizard via `IWorkspacePrefillAi`. Each intent → ONE LLM call → ONE rendering.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Comprehensive regression test required — every existing CapabilityRouter route (the 4 intent capabilities + the 10 chat tools) MUST be verified post-refactor; no behavior regression beyond the duplicate-fire fix.</constraint>
  </constraints>

