    <patterns>
      <pattern name="CapabilityRouter 3-tier" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs">
        Tier 1: deterministic regex / keyword match. Tier 2: LLM intent classification.
        Tier 3: fallback. Preserve intent-detection tiers UNCHANGED. The fix is at the
        OUTPUT routing — after the intent + playbook are resolved, the router consults
        node config `destination` and dispatches to ONE render path.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Path A vs Path B parallelism smell (R5 Gap A)" location="projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/lessons-learned.md">
        When you see two parallel paths handling the "same" user intent, one of them
        is wrong. The structural fix is to collapse into ONE canonical path with the
        rendering destination as data-driven config (not parallel hardcoded paths).
        This task is that collapse.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="PlaybookExecutionEngine routing" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Playbook/">
        After task 025 (Phase A Pillar 4), the engine is the canonical routing surface
        for chat `/summarize`. CapabilityRouter dispatches into the engine; the engine
        executes the playbook; `DeliverOutput` reads node config `destination` and
        publishes to ONE surface.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 SC-18 surfaced that typing `/summarize` produced both a chat-agent
      acknowledgement AND a workspace artifact rendering, AND the chat agent emitted a
      duplicate "Here's the summary..." inline. Two LLM calls, two renderings. R5
      lessons-learned Gap A diagnosed this as parallel-path smell: the chat tool
      bridge invoked a playbook AND the chat agent emitted a duplicate text response.

      Q5 re-shape (this R6 session) put the fix STRUCTURALLY at CapabilityRouter — not at
      the action level via metadata. The router, after resolving intent + playbook,
      consults the playbook node's `destination` (set by tasks 032 + 033) and dispatches
      to ONE render path. The 3-tier intent classification is preserved. The legacy
      "chat acks while workspace also fires" path is removed.

      This depends on Phase A task 025 (which puts `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` on the
      engine instead of the alternate-key bypass) — without that, CapabilityRouter has
      two routing surfaces to coordinate. With task 025 landed + tasks 032/033/040/041
      landed, the canonical route is single-surface and dedup is a clean collapse.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs (MODIFIED — main implementation)</file>
