      <item>Tasks 032 + 033 populate node `destination` — required for the dedup to read.</item>
      <item>Task 041 (schema-aware widget) is the consumer; this task ensures it is the SOLE render path.</item>
      <item>Task 048 Phase B integration test validates dedup end-to-end.</item>
      <item>R5 lessons-learned Gap A is the architectural diagnosis this task structurally fixes.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: BFF code refactoring at central routing surface; NFR-01 binding sensitivity
                 (conversational primacy); R5 Gap A structural fix; comprehensive regression
                 test required
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS: all 12 steps below INCLUDING Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Confirm Prerequisites">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 042 status 🔲. Verify deps complete: Phase A task 025
      (engine routing); Phase B 041 (widget). Verify Spaarke Dev has action `outputSchema`
      + node `destination` populated for migrated actions (smoke query).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Read `CapabilityRouter.cs`, `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs`,
      `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs` IN FULL. Read R5 lessons-learned Gap A in full. Read
      AI-ARCHITECTURE.md and chat-architecture.md for the routing flow contract.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Map the Existing Duplicate-Fire Paths">
      Identify the TWO paths that currently produce parallel output for `/summarize`:
      (a) chat-agent's text response;
      (b) the chat tool bridge → playbook → workspace artifact.
      Document the call chain for each in `notes/task-042-dedup-refactor-evidence.md`.
      Confirm task 025 already routes the playbook chain via the engine (no alternate
      key bypass).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Design the One-Intent-One-Route Surface">
      Design the dedup: after intent resolution + playbook selection, CapabilityRouter
      consults the playbook node's `destination`. If `destination = chat`: the chat-agent
      handles rendering inline; DO NOT also fire workspace artifact. If
      `destination = workspace`: emit PaneEventBus workspace event ONCE; SUPPRESS the
      chat-agent's parallel text response (or, equivalently, emit a thin chat
      acknowledgement that does NOT re-execute the playbook). If
      `destination = form-prefill`: route through `IWorkspacePrefillAi`; chat displays
      a transparent progress indicator only.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement the Dedup">
      Refactor `CapabilityRouter` per the design. Preserve the 3-tier intent
      classification UNCHANGED (Tier 1 deterministic / Tier 2 LLM / Tier 3 fallback).
      The change is in the OUTPUT routing only. Verify the existing middleware pipeline
      (Safety pipeline) is unchanged.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Comprehensive Regression Test Plan">
      Build a regression test plan covering EVERY existing CapabilityRouter route:
      (a) `/summarize` (chat destination) — ONE render in chat;
      (b) `/summarize` (workspace destination if a test playbook is bound) — ONE render
          in workspace;
      (c) All 10 chat tools — no behavior regression;
      (d) Conversational refinement after a playbook output — works normally;
      (e) Follow-up + comparison + context injection — works normally;
      (f) `/clear` and other hard slashes (Phase D) — pass-through unchanged;
      (g) Natural-language summarization (no slash) — same dedup behavior.

      Author unit tests in `CapabilityRouterDedupTests.cs` covering at least cases (a),
      (b), (d).
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build + Verify BFF Publish-Size">
      Per CLAUDE.md §10 bullet 4: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` succeeds
      with 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o
      deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed output; report delta vs prior baseline.
      Expect near-zero delta for a refactor; flag if &gt;+1 MB.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Run Regression Test Suite">
      Run the test plan from Step 6. Capture results in
      `notes/task-042-dedup-refactor-evidence.md`. ANY regression in cases (c)-(g)
      requires diagnosis + fix BEFORE marking complete.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the refactor. Run `adr-check`; verify NFR-01
      (conversational primacy preserved), NFR-13 (safety pipeline preserved), ADR-013
      (facade boundary), ADR-010 (no new top-level DI), ADR-015 (no user message text in
      telemetry), ADR-029 (publish-size delta within budget), ADR-030 (PaneEventBus
      channels unchanged), R5 Gap A (path A/B parallelism eliminated). Both gates MUST
      pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update TASK-INDEX.md: 042 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report completion with
      explicit confirmation of: (a) duplicate-fire eliminated; (b) conversational
      primacy preserved; (c) all 10 chat tools regression-clean; (d) BFF publish-size
      delta within budget.
    </step>
  </steps>

